    "plan_cost_usd": 0.75077015,
    "plan_content": "## Plan: Add `Bun.INI` Namespace\n\nHere's what I found after reading all the relevant source files, and what I'm proposing:\n\n### Files to Create (1)\n- **`src/bun.js/api/INIObject.zig`** — new self-contained INI parser/stringifier, modeled after `JSON5Object.zig` (the closest analog since it also has both `parse` and `stringify`)\n\n### Files to Modify (4)\n1. **`src/bun.js/api/BunObject.zig`** — add `pub const INI`, `@export`, `getINIObject` getter, and `INIObject` import (4 small changes mirroring the YAML/TOML/JSON5 entries)\n2. **`src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject+exports.h`** — add `macro(INI)` between `macro(Glob)` and `macro(JSON5)` (alphabetical: G → I → J)\n3. **`src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject.cpp`** — add `INI BunObject_lazyPropCb_wrap_INI DontDelete|PropertyCallback` to the `bunObjectTable` hash, before `JSONC`\n4. **`packages/bun-types/bun.d.ts`** — add `namespace INI` with JSDoc'd `parse(input: string): Record<string, any>` and `stringify(input: Record<string, any>): string`\n\n### INIObject.zig implementation approach\n- **`parse`**: custom line-by-line parser using `std.mem.splitScalar` + `bun.strings.trim`/`indexOfChar`. Skips `#`/`;` comments, handles `[section]` → nested JS objects, `key=value` → `JSValue` strings. Throws on unterminated `[section` headers.\n- **`stringify`**: uses `wtf.StringBuilder` + two passes over `jsc.JSPropertyIterator(.{.include_value=true})` — first pass for flat `key = value\\n` entries, second pass for `\\n[section]\\nkey = value\\n` nested objects.",
